ource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.523523524413881e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Adam\", \"from\": 244, \"to\": 248}, {\"ngram\": \"his first Olympic medal\", \"from\": 264, \"to\": 287}, {\"ngram\": \"canoe slalom\", \"from\": 293, \"to\": 305}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 320}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Stoke-on-Trent paddler, the fourth-fastest finisher from the semi-finals, put in a superb run save a small error on upstream gate 17, but recovered at the bottom of the course, crossing the finish in 96.84 seconds for the fastest run of the final with three men left to challenge.\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 658, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Trent\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 392}, {\"ngram\": \"the fourth-fastest finisher\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 429}, {\"ngram\": \"the semi\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 443}, {\"ngram\": \"finals\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 450}, {\"ngram\": \"a superb run\", \"from\": 459, \"to\": 471}, {\"ngram\": \"a small error\", \"from\": 477, \"to\": 490}, {\"ngram\": \"upstream gate\", \"from\": 494, \"to\": 507}, {\"ngram\": \"the bottom\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 539}, {\"ngram\": \"the course\", \"from\": 543, \"to\": 553}, {\"ngram\": \"the finish\", \"from\": 564, \"to\": 574}, {\"ngram\": \"96.84 seconds\", \"from\": 578, \"to\": 591}, {\"ngram\": \"the fastest run\", \"from\": 596, \"to\": 611}, {\"ngram\": \"three men\", \"from\": 630, \"to\": 639}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Burgess was still sitting in gold medal position when home favourite Nicolas Gestin, the reigning world silver medallist, left his best run for last, destroying the Briton's leading time in 91.36, 5.48 seconds faster than the British runner-up, with Slovakia's Matej Benus rounding out the podium.\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 957, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 729, \"end\": 743, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Gestin\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nicolas Gestin\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Gestin\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicolas_Gestin\"}, {\"begin\": 886, \"end\": 893, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.6249827336209203, \"rank\": 0.5304266382305213, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 910, \"end\": 918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovakia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.8732002902147363, \"rank\": 0.13775036369038118, \"text\": \"Slovakia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovakia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Slovakia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Burgess\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 667}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medal position\", \"from\": 689, \"to\": 708}, {\"ngram\": \"the reigning world silver medallist\", \"from\": 745, \"to\": 780}, {\"ngram\": \"his best run\", \"from\": 787, \"to\": 799}, {\"ngram\": \"the Briton's leading time\", \"from\": 821, \"to\": 846}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 956}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was redemption for Burgess, who avenged his maiden final from three summers ago in Tokyo, where the now-32-year-old finished fourth and missed out on a medal by just 0.16 seconds.\", \"from\": 959, \"to\": 1141, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1045, \"end\": 1050, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.997375651685519, \"rank\": 0.00263124630393705, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"redemption\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 976}, {\"ngram\": \"Burgess\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 988}, {\"ngram\": \"a medal\", \"from\": 1112, \"to\": 1119}, {\"ngram\": \"just 0.16 seconds\", \"from\": 1123, \"to\": 1140}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was another magical moment for the British paddlers after Kimberley Woods collected bronze in the women's kayak singles on Sunday, and just as she vowed she would do after her own magical moment - was in the stands cheering on her team-mate.\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1387, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1181, \"end\": 1188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.6249827336209203, \"rank\": 0.5304266382305213, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 1204, \"end\": 1219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kimberley Woods\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kimberley_Woods\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"another magical moment\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1172}, {\"ngram\": \"bronze\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"the women's kayak singles\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1265}, {\"ngram\": \"Sunday\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1275}, {\"ngram\": \"her own magical moment\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1340}, {\"ngram\": \"the stands\", \"from\": 1350, \"to\": 1360}, {\"ngram\": \"her team-mate\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1386}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Burgess' jaw dropped when he realised he was guaranteed a medal after Germany's Sideris Tasiadis, who pipped him to Bronze in Tokyo, did not do enough for a podium place in Paris with his 97.27 - and it just became a matter of which colour he would collect.\", \"from\": 1389, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1459, \"end\": 1466